# Task S55-T1: Header and Loaders

## Description
Adjust the header behavior and visuals:
1. Fix the centered title alignment so it doesn't look slightly off due to the logo on the left.
2. Ensure the logo is never completely removed from the header.
3. Introduce an animated logo-based loader state (e.g. Netflix style) to be shown in the header when data is being retrieved (for objects, reports, etc.).
4. Overall, add minor structural enhancements to ensure these actions happen cleanly.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Title spans centered correctly accounting for flexible elements around it.
- Loading states cleanly transition the logo space to an animated logo loader instead of a static "retrieving data" text placeholder in the middle.
